---
const faqs = [
   {
      question: 'What is ai.json?',
      answer: 'ai.json is a configuration file that defines your AI agent settings—skills, rules, prompts, and MCP servers—in one place. aix reads this file and installs the configuration to any supported editor.',
   },
   {
      question: 'Which editors are supported?',
      answer: 'aix supports Claude Code, Cursor, VS Code (with Copilot), Windsurf, Codex, and Zed. Each editor has its own configuration format, and aix handles the translation automatically.',
   },
   {
      question: 'How do I share config with my team?',
      answer: 'Use the extends field in ai.json to reference configurations from GitHub repositories, npm packages, or local files. Team members can inherit shared standards while adding their own customizations.',
   },
   {
      question: 'Is aix free?',
      answer: 'Yes. aix is open source under the MIT license. You can use it for personal projects, commercial work, or contribute to its development on GitHub.',
   },
   {
      question: 'How do I add custom skills or rules?',
      answer: 'Run aix add skill <url> to add skills from GitHub, npm, or local files. Skills can include rules (behavioral guidelines), prompts (reusable instructions), and MCP server configurations.',
   },
   {
      question: 'Where does aix store configuration?',
      answer: 'aix stores the ai.json file in your project root. When you run aix install, it writes editor-specific configuration to each editor\'s expected location (e.g., .cursorrules for Cursor).',
   },
];
---

<section class="faq border-t border-gray-800/50 bg-gray-900/20 py-24 md:py-28">
   <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-balance text-center text-3xl font-bold text-gray-50 md:text-4xl">
         Frequently asked <span class="text-gradient">questions</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mb-12 max-w-xl text-pretty text-center text-lg text-gray-300 md:text-xl">
         Everything you need to know about aix.
      </p>

      <div class="faq__list space-y-4">
         {faqs.map((faq, index) => (
            <details
               class="faq__item group rounded-2xl border border-gray-800/70 bg-gray-900/40 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-500/30 hover:bg-gray-900/70"
               style={`animation: fadeInUp 0.5s ease-out ${index * 0.1}s both`}
            >
               <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 text-left font-medium text-gray-100 transition-colors hover:text-accent-300 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
                  <span>{faq.question}</span>
                  <svg
                     class="size-5 shrink-0 text-gray-400 transition-all duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 group-open:text-accent-400"
                     fill="none"
                     viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                     stroke="currentColor"
                     stroke-width="2"
                  >
                     <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                  </svg>
               </summary>
               <div class="border-t border-gray-800 px-5 pb-5 pt-4 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                  {faq.answer}
               </div>
            </details>
         ))}
      </div>
   </div>
</section>

<style>
   @keyframes fadeInUp {
      from {
         opacity: 0;
         transform: translateY(20px);
      }
      to {
         opacity: 1;
         transform: translateY(0);
      }
   }
</style>
